  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "This example underscores the importance of nuanced questioning and highlights the potential risks and safety implications of over-relying on AI-generated information.Studies highlight both the benefits and drawbacks of using generative AI in interpreting health data.",
    "Recent advancements in generative AI and ML are transforming the diagnosis and treatment of rare genetic disorders [47].",
    "AI-powered tools can analyze facial images and genetic data to identify potential diagnoses and accurately rank causal genes [48,49].",
    "Other AI systems demonstrate the ability to integrate multiple data sources, including clinical notes and genetic information, to expedite genome interpretation and narrow down candidate diagnoses [50,51].",
    "These technologies enhance diagnostic accuracy by combining various data types, showing great potential in reducing the \"diagnostic odyssey\" faced by patients with rare diseases, lowering costs, and speeding up case reviews [52,53].These examples underscore the importance of using generative AI as a supplementary tool, rather than a standalone solution."
  ],
